Name: Kinnaree Thai Cuisine

Name: Kinnaree Thai Cuisine
Review Text: Best thai that I had around the Jordaan so far. The sweet & spicy curry was lovely and there’s a tofu option for every sauce. A nice selection of wines as well.

Review Text: A very cute restaurant. The fish cakes were soso, the rest if the food that we orderedwas delicious, and the amuse from the house was very creative and tasty way to start our dinner. The service was good. I would definitely recommend friends to go here!

Name: Kinnaree Thai Cuisine
Review Text:
Super cozy, delicate and modern atmosphere. One of those places where you feel it’s unique and a speciality to eat there. Ordered the Kwang Prik Gang, ate venison with black pepper sauce and cashews. Super combination super tender
The salmon in red curry is also a delight
